Healthy-Me Back-End Project README

Welcome to the Healthy-Me back-end project! This project is designed to provide a platform for managing and tracking healthy food choices for users. The back-end is responsible for handling the data related to foods, categories, and users. This README will guide you through the project setup, structure, and functionalities.

we have 3 tables:
foods
categories
users


Technologies Used:
Node.js
Express.js
MongoDB

Getting Started:
Prerequisites
Before you begin, ensure you have the following prerequisites:

Node.js and npm installed
MongoDB installed and running


Installation:
Clone this repository: git clone https://github.com/your-username/healthy-me-backend.git
Navigate to the project directory: cd healthy-me-backend
Install dependencies: npm install
Copy and configure the necessary configuration files in the config/ directory.
Run migrations to set up the database schema: npm run migrate
Seed initial data: npm run seed
Start the server: npm start

API Endpoints:
GET /foods: Get a list of all food items.
GET /foods/:id: Get details of a specific food item.
POST /foods: Add a new food item.
PUT /foods/:id: Update details of a specific food item.
DELETE /foods/:id: Delete a specific food item.
...
Refer to the API documentation for a complete list of endpoints and their functionalities.

Authentication:
The project uses JWT (JSON Web Tokens) for authentication. Users can register, log in, and receive a token to authenticate their API requests.
